<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>Mastodon Home Timeline</title><link>https://mastodon.social</link><description>RSS feed for the Mastodon Home timeline</description><docs>http://www.rssboard.org/rss-specification</docs><generator>python-feedgen</generator><lastBuildDate>Sun, 09 Jul 2023 04:21:12 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Björn Brembs</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@brembs/110671534984263730</link><description>I've seen many of the reasons why &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/Elsevier" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Elsevier&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is called &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/Evilsevier" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Evilsevier&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; by virtually everybody.But this really takes the cake:&lt;a href="https://www.designresearchsociety.org/articles/the-future-of-design-studies-journal" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;designresearchsociety.org/arti&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;cles/the-future-of-design-studies-journal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;If you ever needed a single, 5min explanation of one of the many reasons why we need to replace academic journals,, this is the one.Here are the other reasons:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5526634" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5526634&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110677228901664031</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 07:14:49 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Berna Devezer</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@devezer/110669058257656262</link><description>One key point we make is that we should stop equating scientific discovery to statistical inference(s) made in a given paper and expecting each paper to produce a fact-like discovery, and start reconceptualizing discovery as a potential outcome of a long process of exploration. Discoveries do not live in papers, they exist at the community-/system-level. We are not promised a discovery just because we hope to make one.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110677241140100910</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 07:17:56 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Björn Brembs</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@brembs/110673623892687471</link><description>Just in case you ever wondered what a "cooperation" with &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/Elsevier" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Elsevier&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; looks like:"Elsevier publishes many journals 'in cooperation' with different societies and these aim to bring reciprocal benefits; however this does not give those organisations a role in the appointment of journal editors." &lt;a href="https://www.designresearchsociety.org/articles/the-future-of-design-studies-journal" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;designresearchsociety.org/arti&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;cles/the-future-of-design-studies-journal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/Evilsevier" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Evilsevier&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110677255595912796</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 07:21:36 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Shane O'Mara</title><link>https://mstdn.science/@shaneomara/110673424653134849</link><description>One cheer for this - a new drug for Alzheimer’s that kinda works a bit (if I understand things correctly, Lecanemab slows disease progression, with a delay of c. five months over an 18-month timeframe; this doesn’t seem like much, but it is the first really positive signal in this area since forever. The hope is that this will trigger a bout of new research - often new treatments are not so good, but improve dramatically over time.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mstdn.science/tags/alzheimer" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;alzheimer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mstdn.science/tags/lecanemab" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;lecanemab&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110677412613758195</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 08:01:32 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Daniel Lakens</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@lakens/110673235790443767</link><description>Understanding p-values is not difficult, but it does take more time (say 2 hours initially, rehearsing it 4 times for 30 minutes) than people invest, which is the only barrier to getting people to understand them. This material should be all you need. &lt;a href="https://lakens.github.io/statistical_inferences/01-pvalue.html" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;lakens.github.io/statistical_i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;nferences/01-pvalue.html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110677414503676578</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 08:02:01 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Aussie News :firstnations:</title><link>https://tictoc.social/@aussienews/110677643921429961</link><description>The story of my face &lt;a href="https://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/the-story-of-my-face/xqjdn1wth" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;sbs.com.au/news/article/the-st&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;ory-of-my-face/xqjdn1wth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://tictoc.social/tags/Indigenous" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Indigenous&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://tictoc.social/tags/Culture" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Culture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110677978898468110</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 10:25:33 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>katejjeffery</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@katejjeffery/110676824039517801</link><description>Immigration minister has cartoon murals painted over at children’s asylum centre - wtf&lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/jul/07/robert-jenrick-has-cartoon-murals-painted-over-at-childrens-asylum-centre" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/j&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;ul/07/robert-jenrick-has-cartoon-murals-painted-over-at-childrens-asylum-centre&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110678169911451685</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 11:14:08 +0000</pubDate></item><item><link>https://neuromatch.social/@admin/110675551850902010</link><description>&lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://neuromatch.social/@jonny" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;jonny&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://neuromatch.social/@manisha" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;manisha&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://neuromatch.social/@lina" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;lina&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sp