were paid vs 86% of the men.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110678793841643001</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 13:52:48 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>David Schoppik</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@schoppik/110678903812894443</link><description>Don't miss the &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://mastodon.social/tags/zebrafish" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;zebrafish&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; digest for May/June! &lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://biologists.social/@ZebrafishRock/110678655738918450" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;biologists.social/@ZebrafishRo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;ck/110678655738918450&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110678903812894443</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 14:20:46 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/110680725344414908</link><description>New paper!&lt;br/&gt;In vivo ephaptic coupling allows memory network formation&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1093/cercor/bhad251" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;doi.org/10.1093/cercor/bhad251&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Neurons are like members of a huge orchestra.  They need to coordinate to play a song.  Ephaptic coupling spreads influences at the speed of light.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">110680725457977157</guid><pubDate>Sat, 08 Jul 2023 22:04:01 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/110681244222450317</link><description>Closing the loop in psychiatric deep brain stimulation: physiology, psychometrics, and plasticity&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41386-023-01643-y" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span c